clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the in hospital short term up to 48 hours management of severe hypertension when rapid but quickly reversible emergency reduction of blood pressure is clinically indicated including malignant hypertension with deteriorating end organ function

contraindications.disease: The most likely reaction of overdose would be excessive hypotension which should be treated with drug discontinuation and appropriate supportive measures
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Fenoldopam is an agonist at D sub 1 sub like dopamine receptors binds to alpha sub 2 sub adrenoceptors increasing renal blood flow
